HEADWORD: Transfugitive
<hw>Trans*fu"gi*tive</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>transfuga</ets>;
<ets>trans</ets> across, over + <ets>fugere</ets> to flee.]</ety>
<def>One who flees from one side to another; hence, a deserter; a
turncoat; an apostate.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

